## Design, Branding, and Tech Stack Standards (Overview)

- Follow the documented stack conventions (e.g. Next.js 14/15, FastAPI, TypeScript strict, Tailwind CSS 4.x, Supabase/PostgreSQL, Prisma, vector stores) and prefer their official patterns and guides.
- Use design tokens from the shared UI package (e.g. `@repo/ui/tokens`) instead of hard-coded hex values.
- Respect Sentra brand conventions (including any required signatures or identifiers) when creating new UI components or files.

If you are unsure about a pattern, propose consulting official documentation and existing code in this monorepo rather than inventing a new approach.

